To be able to determine the energy of each peak accurately and to be able to separate nearby peaks, it is essential that the width of each peak is as narrow as possible. Obviously this requires a light yield of the scintillator, and a light collection efficiency, that are homogeneous over the volume of the scintillator. Assuming a Poisson distribution with average Ne for the number of photoelectrons, the relative energy resolution FWHM of the scintillator will be given by
